Speaker 2: So, your wife won't see them?

Speaker 1: Well, I wasn't expecting, I wasn't even expecting any, what's that?

Speaker 1: Yeah, well, I just don't want her to see, like she was trying, like she was at home and she opened up my mail, I guess.

Speaker 2: Oh, copy that.

Speaker 1: I didn't know it was coming and she's like on your website, like asking for my password and shit, so.

Speaker 2: Okay, I understand loud and clear.

Speaker 1: Alright, man, we'll take care of it for you, but if you like, you can always give us another address or something.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: Right, yeah.

Speaker 2: Well, like I said, I haven't had her for two months, but also I wasn't expecting it either, and it was like a surprise.

Speaker 1: She just called me freaking out.

Speaker 2: I just don't want her to go into the account, because I can see her, because she's seeing it was my phone number as well.

Speaker 1: She obviously knows my email address, so.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but legally we can't have anybody else adjust anything on the account if it's not the actual patient.

Speaker 1: No, but she could go in there and she could put my email address and my phone number, but I guess it would come back to my phone.

Speaker 2: Correct, yeah, but we wouldn't be able to change anything or alter any information or anything like that, because she's not the patient.

Speaker 1: So, even if she did do that, she still wouldn't be able to change anything.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: Well, I forgot about that, but just to be safe, I mean, if I have to come back, I will, but just to be safe, if I could just cancel it and get rid of the account in general.

Speaker 2: Okay, I got you.

Speaker 1: Is there a way you can just make it disappear?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I can do it for you now.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you shouldn't be able to find it, it should just deactivate it, so.
